&lt;p>To make &lt;a href="https://www.sg.ethz.ch/projects/pharmaceutical-supply-chain-resilience/">our research on drug shortage mitigation and prevention&lt;/a> accessible to a broader audience, we created an AI-generated podcast. The podcast discusses our findings on pharmaceutical supply chain resilience (see the &lt;a href="https://www.sg.ethz.ch/projects/pharmaceutical-supply-chain-resilience/">project page&lt;/a> for a list of publications).&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Efficiency and resilience: Key drivers of distribution network growth</title><link>https://www.sg.ethz.ch/publications/2024/amico2024efficiency-and-resilience/</link><pubDate>Fri, 23 Aug 2024 08:43:57 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.sg.ethz.ch/publications/2024/amico2024efficiency-and-resilience/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Tracing Opioids Across the US: A High-Resolution Pharmaceutical Distribution Dataset</title><link>https://www.sg.ethz.ch/publications/2024/amico2024tracing-opioids-across/</link><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2024 11:01:11 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.sg.ethz.ch/publications/2024/amico2024tracing-opioids-across/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Adapting to disruptions: Managing supply chain resilience through product rerouting</title><link>https://www.sg.ethz.ch/publications/2024/amico2024adapting-to-disruptions/</link><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.sg.ethz.ch/publications/2024/amico2024adapting-to-disruptions/</guid><description>&lt;p>See &lt;a href="https://www.sg.ethz.ch/news/2024_01_resilience-published/">our blog post&lt;/a> on this research.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Paper on Supply Chain Resilience Published in Science Advances</title><link>https://www.sg.ethz.ch/news/2024_01_resilience-published/</link><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.sg.ethz.ch/news/2024_01_resilience-published/</guid><description>&lt;p>Excited to share our research published in &lt;em>Science Advances&lt;/em>, focusing on a vital aspect of modern logistics: pharmaceutical supply chain resilience (&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1126/sciadv.adj1194">Link to Paper&lt;/a> ðŸ“‘).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The COVID-19 pandemic and subsequent global events have underscored the critical need to enhance supply chain resilience. To address this challenge, our study introduces the concept of &amp;lsquo;reroute flexibility,&amp;rsquo; best understood through an analogy to a road network.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Picture a distribution network for products as a network of roads and intersections.
The distribution pathsâ€”routes products take to their destinationsâ€”are like journeys on these roads. During disruptions, one might consider building new roads to improve flow, but this is obviously too slow, prehitively expensive and overall wasteful. A much better solution is for the driver or navigation system to use other, possible but never before used roads to reach the destination.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>